defaultQ: defaultHow can local authorities attract greater investment from the private sector for the delivery and maintenance of local transpdefaultort infrastructure? What scope is there for the use of alternative funding streams?default&#xa0;
defaultLocal government is one of the 
defaultfew 
defaultparts of the public sector that uses its resources to increase growth and productivity, both of which are critical to funding services. 
defaultCouncils need financial autonomy to maximise their assets and invest to support growth
default and infrastructure
default.
default&#xa0;
defaultThe LGA’s Rewiring Public Service
defaults
default campaign advocates devolving certain tax and spending decisions to the local level, so that public services can be integrated to deliver better results. 
defaultThis would benefit the economy by moving away from top-down solutions that don’t fit everywhere, inste
defaultad allowing individual areas to play to its strengths. This would result in a more resilient economy overall by making each area stronger instead of accepting that some will always be dependent on others. 
default&#xa0;
defaultSuch a system would incentivise local growth 
defaultand 
defaultinvestment, which 
defaultjoin
defaulting
default up whole place decision-making to deliver more effective, better value services.
default&#xa0;
default It could bring together decision making on health, 
defaulttransport, 
defaulthousing, education and emergency services and include closer working with business and
default the voluntary sector.
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultDevolving in this way would mean breaking away from our busted system of local government finance and allowing local areas to raise funds in ways that make sense in that area, not relying on Council Tax and Business rates. 
default&#xa0;
defaultLocal p
defaulteople would get the results and local services they care about by giving them power over local taxation and how their taxes are spent.
default&#xa0;
defaultDespite the 43% funding cuts (across the life of the current Parliament) which councils are being forced to endure, local government is still 
defaultdelivering and innovating on major in
defaultfrastructure projects that will 
defaultradically transform the economic viability of
default an area. Major projects such as the Mersey
default 
defaultGateway, will drastically reduce congestion and kick-start a major 20 year regeneration
default 
defaultprogramme. The new bridge is being procured as a Public Private Partnership with over
default 
default70 per cent 
defaultof the cost being funded b
defaulty the private sector (financed through tolls
default 
defaultcollected).
default&#xa0;
defaultWolverhampton and Staffordshire councils jointly funded the development of critical road
default 
defaultinfrastructure, which involved £36 million of prudential borrowing, which helped give Tata Ltd
default 
defaultcertainty and 
defaultconfidence in making the investment decision for a £400million investment in a
default 
defaultnew manufacturing plant for Jaguar Land Rover.
default&#xa0;
defaultThe LGA is in discussion with HM Treasury on the r
defaulte-creat
defaultion of a
default thriving market in municipal bonds
default 
defaultwhich England once had and m
defaultost other countries
default still have. Such as bond market would 
defaultfree local government borrowing from Treasury
default 
defaultrestrictions because it already complies with
default 
defaultappropriate prudential rules
default; and 
defaultallow access to alternative sources of finance
default, 
defaultincluding the creation o
defaultf a local government bond
default 
defaultagency and the right to develop earn-back deals.
default This
default would allow places to reinvest the proceeds
default 
defaultof additional growth in local services and measures
default 
defaultto promote further growth
default.
