defaultQ: defaultHow clear are the lines of accountability for defaultlocal decision making on transport expenditure?default&#xa0;
defaultAs always, councils have shown that they can work pragmatically to ensure clear lines of accountability on their spending decisions. As mentioned 
defaultpreviously
default, the Government has complicated matters by introdu
defaultcing Local Transport Boards
default,
default then then transferring future transport spending decisions to Local Enterprise Partnerships. 
defaultAs LEPs develop in this way, the issue of accountability needs to be considered. 
defaultCouncils are working with LEP
default partner
default to identify way
defaults to ensure that there is still democratic accountability within the new system.  
default&#xa0;
defaultWhilst councils welcome the move towards greater devolution of decision-making to the local level, they remain frustrated by the fact that the permanent secretary of the D
defaulte
defaultpartment for 
defaultT
defaultransport 
defaultremains
default accountable to P
defaultarliament
default for local transport investment. Given the spending is to benefit local residents and businesses, the LGA firmly believes that it should be at the local level where the public can 
defaulthold decision-makers to account.
